Federal Home Loan Bank of Atlanta Home Loan Products







HomeEducation & EventsEvent Calendar













Federal Home Loan Bank of Atlanta Home Loan Products

.  Please Note --> This is a Past Event!! .


Date:

4/5/2012

Time:

11:30 AM TO 1:30 PM



 BWI Marriott Hotel  1743 West Nursery Road  Baltimore, MD  21240



Phone:


410-269-5977




Event Description:

As Maryland banks continue to face lingering effects from the financial crisis, it is critical that bankers make the most of resources at their disposal. One important resource comes in the form of affordable housing products and services that are available through financial partnerships with Federal Home Loan Bank of Atlanta (FHLBank Atlanta). The Bank’s Affordable Housing products provide real estate equity which supports the funding of rental and ownership housing development, acquisition and rehabilitation. The products, which focus on community stability, foreclosure recovery and weatherization/accessibility rehabilitation, will assist Maryland financial institutions in growing loan production, managing transactional credit risk, and building new business relationships. 
To learn how you can put these products to work in your community, join the Maryland Bankers Association on April 5, 2012, from 11:30 a.m. to 1:30 p.m., for a luncheon and education session about the latest FHLBank Atlanta affordable housing products. John Bond, director of the FHLBank Atlanta will host the luncheon at the BWI Airport Marriott at 1743 West Nursery Road Linthicum, Maryland. For details please contact Jason Clayton at jclayton@fhlbatl.com. 
We encourage you to invite your senior mortgage lender or Community Reinvestment Act officer to attend this session with you. 
Please confirm your attendance by registering online by March 30, 2012. 


